Police in Kericho on Wednesday launched a manhunt for the killers of a 24-year-old man. Donald Kipkurui was beaten to death on Monday in Chemugusu village, near Brooke Bond market in Ainamoi constituency. Kipkurui was with Emmanuel Kiprotich, also 24, who was beaten and seriously wounded. Kiprotich has been admitted to Kericho Level 4 Hospital in a critical condition. Kipkurui's body is at the same hospital's mortuary. It is not clear why the two were beaten. Speaking to journalists in Kericho police station office, deputy OCPD Allan Mwangi said they are looking for the killers. "We have clues that will help the police to arrest the suspects," the deputy OCPD said. He urged members of the public to volunteer information that could lead to the arrest of those who beat the two. Edited by A.N